channel.title: Compiler error
channel.description:
I recently just fixed my 64bit compiler error while using Delta base. Now that I can actually compile I have a compiler error that I've never seen before nor can I find anything on google.
[img]http://puu.sh/5GWBj.png[/img]
(BTW the compiler I'm using for up to date java on 64-bit win7 is: @echo off "C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.7.0_45\bin\javac.exe" *.java pause)
^^^took me awhile to find that^^^

item.title: Compiler error
item.dc:creator: @Bl3nd Bl3nd
item.description:
@Bl3nd wrote:

Somewhere in that file, ‘bw’ is already being defined. So since it’s already being defined i’d just go and delete that thing. If you do need it, then change the ‘bw’ part.

You cannot have the same name for a variable that’s already in the same file.

lol edit: Why are you making that variable 6 times? It only needs to be made once in the whole file.
